t="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>mах dær zæǧʒystæm ærgom</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>мы тоже скажем открыто</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>we will also say frankly</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 65</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>de ʽrgom næm ma razdax</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не обращай к нам лица</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>do not turn your face to us</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>q˳yddag rаrgom īs</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>дело раскрылось</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the case was solved</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Nartæn sæ žwar ærgom rašydi</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Нартовское божество открыто вышло (к народу)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Nart divinity overtly came to people</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I 179</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ærgom ʒyrdy kʼæm næj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в откровенной речи нет ничего зазорного</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there is nothing shameful in a frank speech</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 237</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ærgomæj saxarmæ nal cydī</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не мог уже явно войти в город</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>[Jesus] could no more openly enter into the city</q></cit><bibl><ref target=""/><biblScope>Марк 1 45</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>axæm sūsæg nīcy īs, ḱī næ rargom wa</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>нет ничего тайного, что не сделалось бы явным</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>for there is nothing hid, which shall not be manifested</q></cit><bibl><ref target=""/><biblScope>Марк 4 22</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æxe næmæ næ sirgon kænʒænæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>он нам не откроется</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he will not open to us</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>34%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>Batraz Boræfærnugmæ je ʽrgon raxatgæj ʒoruj...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Батраз, повернувшись лицом к Борафарнугу, говорит...</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Facing Borafarnug, Batraz says…</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>mах dær zæǧʒystæm ærgom</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>мы тоже скажем открыто</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>we will also say frankly</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 65</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Сращение префикса %iær%i- с <xr><ref target="#entry_kom"/></xr> ‘рот’ (ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_cæskom"/></xr> ‘лицо’ и <xr><ref target="#entry_gom"/></xr> gom ‘открытый’). Префикс %iær%i-, весьма употребительный в качестве живого преверба (ср. %iær-gom kænyn%i ‘обнажить’), в старых сращениях известен лишь в немногих случаях; кроме %iærgom%i ср. в особенности <xr><ref target="#entry_ærtax"/></xr> ‘капля’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ærtæx"/></xr> ‘роса’ и д. <xr><ref target="#entry_ærtajun"/></xr> ‘купаться’. С <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>ær-gom</w></mentioned> можно сопоставить <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>an-kam-</w></mentioned> в %i’nkm’ny%i ‘открыто’, ‘в лицо’, от *%ikam%i ‘рот’, ‘лицо’, но с другим префиксом (%ian%i- из %iham%i). См. <xr><ref target="#entry_kom"/><ref target="#entry_gom"/></xr>. Для семантики (‘явный’ — ‘лицо’) ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>čiϑra-</w></mentioned> 1. ‘явный’, 2. ‘лицо’. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>а̀rgama</w><gloss><q>явно</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘гласно’ (<bibl corresp=""><biblScope>%bХр. Вост. V 192%b</biblScope></bibl>) и <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/><w>argam</w></mentioned> id. представляют, очевидно, старое заимствование из осетинского (аланского). Ср. д. <xr><ref target="#entry_irux"/></xr> irux.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_JA"><biblScope>1936, стр. 202—203</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The fusion of the prefix %iær%i- with <xr><ref target="#entry_kom"/></xr> ‘mouth’ (compare <xr><ref target="#entry_cæskom"/></xr> ‘face’ and<xr><ref target="#entry_gom"/></xr> gom ‘open’). The prefix %iær%i-, which is quite common as a modern preverb (compare %iær-gom kænyn%i ‘to bare’), is known just in few ancient fusions; besides %iærgom%i especially compare <xr><ref target="#entry_ærtax"/></xr> ‘drop’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ærtæx"/></xr> ‘dew’ and Digor <xr><ref target="#entry_ærtajun"/></xr> ‘to bath’. One may compare the following with <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>ær-gom</w></mentioned> : <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>an-kam-</w></mentioned> in %i’nkm’ny%i ‘overtly’, ‘frankly’, from *%ikam%i ‘mouth’, ‘face’, but with another prefix (%ian%i- from %iham%i). See <xr><ref target="#entry_kom"/><ref target="#entry_gom"/></xr>. As for semantics (‘overt’ — ‘face’), compare <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>čiϑra-</w></mentioned> 1. ‘overt’, 2. ‘face’. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>а̀rgama</w><gloss><q>overtly</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘openly’ (<bibl corresp=""><biblScope>Xristianskij vostok, vol. 192</biblScope></bibl>) and <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/><w>argam</w></mentioned> id. represent apparently ancient borrowing from Ossetic (Alan). Compare Digor <xr><ref target="#entry_irux"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_JA"><biblScope>1936, стр. 202—203</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>